<!-- By Dependent Issues (Action) - DO NOT REMOVE -->

There are several natural orders here. I chose to group by function, then by interval, then have preimage before image. I don't mind if you reorder lemmas in a different predictable order, but I won't have time to do it myself before Sunday.

I see preimages vs images as being a greater distinction than which intervals you're talking about (if only because there might soon be a way to autogenerate the `Iic` lemmas from the `Ici` ones, etc...)

I've reordered the lemmas according to `preimage` vs `image` and also made sure that each series came in order of
* `Ici`
* `Ioi`
* `Iic`
* `Iio`
* `Icc`
* `Ico`
* `Ioc`
* `Ioo`
